data.meta_description: Aug 1, 2018 - Surrounded by Carillon Historical Park’s 65-acre campus, with its commanding view of the Great Miami River, Deeds Carillon (Ohio’s largest carillon) provides an iconic setting for a wedding ceremony. It was built in 1942 by Reinhard & Hofmeister of New York, the same architectural firm responsible for Rockefeller Center. Please contact our Facilities Rental Department at (***) ***-**** Ext. 106 or ev****@*****. See more ideas about ohio, dayton, dayton ohio.
